      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A concerned mother presents her infant who exhibits signs consistent with aplastic anemia. After a thorough clinical evaluation, the decision is made to proceed with a bone marrow biopsy to further investigate the cause of the anemia. In infants, from which bone should the bone marrow sample be taken for biopsy?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q5020112",
